                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Hyderabad, June 25: The Andhra Pradesh high court has granted conditional bail to two persons accused in the Satyam scam. A CBI counsel said S. Gopalakrishnan, the Pricewaterhouse auditor who signed the companys financial reports, and Prabhakara Gupta, a former internal auditor, were granted bail. However, Justice Raja Elango ordered them to appear before the investigating officer everyday and cooperate with the probe.                            
	 Mumbai, June 25: Tata Motors will start rolling out light and medium commercial vehicles from its new plant in South Africa by the end of this fiscal, managing director (India operations) Prakash M. Telang said.                            
	 New Delhi, June 25: The government today deferred a decision on imposing import duty on refined sugar in the wake of high food inflation.                                                                                                                          
